“The sea is ours”: Bolivia, which has no access to the sea, hopes that the court will reopen the way to the Pacific
Marines are patrolling the headquarters of the Navy in La Paz.
On public buildings are hung navy blue flags.
The maritime bases from Lake Titicaca to the Amazon are covered with the slogan: “We have the right to the sea.
