Morales’s aggressive rhetoric from the Chileans shattered all the good will that may have remained, she explained.
Talks between Bolivia and Chile will continue at some point, but after that it will be extremely difficult to participate in the discussions.
The country has not exchanged ambassadors since 1962.
Former President Eduardo Rodriguez Veltzé, Bolivian representative in The Hague, rejected the idea that the court had taken a decision unusually quickly.
Monday will provide Bolivia with “an extraordinary opportunity for a new period of relations with Chile” and the opportunity to “end 139 years of disagreements with mutual benefits,” he said.
